title: For Sale:  Colt Official Police Post-war first year production 99%+
location: Spartanburg, Greenville, Woodruff, Greenville, South Carolina
postcontent:
Colt Official Police Post-war first year production - 1947 in 99%" condition

Made from 1947 to 1969.

Colt decided to rename the Army Special to more reflect the actual buyers of the gun, so the Army Special name was changed to the Official Police.

The 1947 post-war version had a ramped and serrated front sight, a new shaped hammer with grooves, and the new cylinder retention system.



That was just what the gun was, THE official police issue revolver for a great many police departments like the New York City Police, Boston Police, and Federal agencies like the FBI and Treasury Department.

The Official Police would serve as a prime police issue gun into the 1960s, and was highly favored by private guard services, industrial plant guards, and civilian gun owners wanting a powerful and strong revolver.

title: For Sale:  Obama's REAL strategy with background checks.
location: Obama - On the Soap Box Again., North Carolina, United States
postcontent:
Well, Obama's executive order on background checks is out, and, as expected, it's nothing but 100% redundant to existing federal law. People engaged in the business of selling firearms must have a dealers license and perform background checks. Yeah, no kidding. That's only been the existing federal law for decades. The net practical effect of this executive order is nill. Private sellers who are not "engaged in the business" of selling firearms still do not need an FFL and do not need to run background checks. 

The rather obvious fact is that Obama doesn't really care about background checks themselves. They are a means to an end. For anyone who doubts this see the Enforcement of the Brady Act Reports which neatly break down how many checks were run, how many denials there were and, among other things, how many people were prosecuted for lying on form 4473 or for any other reason related to a NICS transaction. Here's a highlight: For 2010, the last year I could find the report, out of 72,659 denied NICS checks 62 people were prosecuted for any reason. No, that's not an error or a typo. 62 prosecutions out of 72,659 denials. So, clearly, the Obama DOJ does not care about prosecuting people who attempt to illegally obtain guns. So, why is Obama signing high profile but completely redundant executive orders that serve no practical purpose? Simple: Political grandstanding to start a new push for universal background checks legislation. Universal background checks are not the ultimate goal however. So, what is? Dramatically expanding the list of prohibited persons of course. Step 1: Prohibit any sales that don't go through NICS. Step 2: Expand the classes of persons prohibited at every opportunity. Step 3: repeat step 2 over and over. 

The first clue to this can be seen in Obama's call to add persons on the no fly list to the prohibited persons categories. It's worth noting that no due process of law whatsoever is required to place someone on this list. Who is on the list is classified. How they got on the list is classified. Ted Kennedy was on the list. The difference between you and Ted is that Ted was a high powered Senator and got off the list with a phone call. For you it will take 2 years and $50K in legal fees. Of course the no fly list is a small step and is not the end of it. Since the Supreme court has affirmed an individual right to keep and bear arms, the only way that gun prohibitionists can really reach their goals is to keep adding categories of prohibited persons. Sure, they might get local "assault weapons bans" and "high capacity" magazine bans but their ultimate goal of total or even serious gun restriction is off the table, unless they simply add people to the prohibited persons categories, which the supreme court has upheld. First it will be the 'no-fly' list. Next it will be anyone who has a diagnosis of "mental illness". That includes every child who has ever been prescribed an ADHD medication and everybody who has ever been prescribed an anxiety or other psychiatric medication. Vets with PTSD? You better damn well believe it: PROHIBITED. The "mentally ill" catchall will prohibit 60+ million people all by itself. Next it will be some class of misdemeanor, perhaps DUI, then speeding violations, etc. The 'logic' will be: "If you can't obey the traffic laws, you can't be trusted with a gun". As you add to the prohibited person's categories, fewer and fewer people will enjoy the right and fewer and fewer people will be politically active in protecting it. Eventually changes on the Supreme court will permit complete reversal of Heller and McDonald. That's the endgame and it will come faster than you think. So, all I can say is: If you are OK with asking your government permission to exercise your rights, sooner or later it's going to say NO. 

**Since somebody emailed and asked, here is how the law defines a dealer in firearms, and no, Obama cannot change the definition with an executive order.

18 U.S.C. § 921(a)(21)(C)

" (21) The term “engaged in the business” means

(C) as applied to a dealer in firearms, as defined in section 921(a)(11)(A), a person who devotes time, attention, and labor to dealing in firearms as a regular course of trade or business with the principal objective of livelihood and profit through the repetitive purchase and resale of firearms, but such term shall not include a person who makes occasional sales, exchanges, or purchases of firearms for the enhancement of a personal collection or for a hobby, or who sells all or part of his personal collection of firearms;"

Note the specific exclusion for "occasional sales, exchanges, or purchases of firearms for the enhancement of a personal collection or for a hobby, or who sells all or part of his personal collection of firearms". 

Finally, in response to someone elses question, no, in my opinion: If you are truly considered a dealer in firearms under federal law but don't have a license, simply asking to see a permit will NOT satisfy your obligations. You must hold an FFL in addition to complying with the Brady Act and all other dealer requirements. Simply requiring a permit from your buyers is not a substitute for an FFL and all that goes along with it.

Disclaimer: I am not a lawyer and this is not legal advice. For legal advice consult an attorney.

title: For Trade:  Information about the ramifications of Obama's Executive Order, and how it applies to Armslist.
postcontent:
I've read the ATF Guidance on Imperial King Obama's Gun Decree closely
When I look through it closely it really does not appear to require FFLs or background checks for private sales. There are various things that define you as an ‘unlicensed dealer’, including:

1) A business card,
2) Representing yourself as a source of firearms for customers,
3) Taking orders, and offering to buy a specific firearm to immediately resell to that ordering person.
4) Repeatedly selling and then restocking the same model and make firearm,
5) Accepting credit cards, getting business insurance on your stock, and other similar business related activities.
6) — and this is the money one — As a general rule, you will need a license if you repetitively buy and sell firearms with the principal motive of making a profit. In contrast, if you only make occasional sales of firearms from your personal collection, you do not need to be licensed.

I guess this law can be abused, just like any and all other laws can be abused. But if things are as represented in the guidance, Armlist and Gunbroker and all these sorts of websites — and private sales at gun shows — should be fine.

Here is the actual guidance. Note that it was published Jan 1, 2016, so the ATF had a heads-up on today's Imperial Decree:

https://www.atf.gov/file/100871/download
